The transaction represents IMCD's commitment to increase its position in the chemicals market in Latin America, and aligns with its strategy to expand its presence and distribution network in Brazil. IMCD Brazil Trade and Industry Chemicals Ltda, formerly known as Makeni Chemicals Comercio e Industria de Produtos Quimicos Ltda, was founded in 1981. The company specialises in import, marketing and sale of more than 400 chemical and petrochemical products and raw materials with applications in the adhesive and plastics, chemical process, construction, cosmetics, health, hygiene, nutrition, and paints segments. The company operates a distribution center with storage capacity of 4,000 m2 of solids and 1,300 m3 of bulk liquids in the municipality of Diadema (Sao Paulo state), and a branch in the municipality of Simoes Filho (Bahia state). Makeni is an exclusive representative in Brazil of BASF, Celanese, Clariant, Eastman, Evonik, Lyondell, Oxea and Shinetsu. IMCD Group BV, established in 1995, focuses on sale, marketing and distribution of specialty chemicals and food ingredients for the detergents, pharmaceuticals, personal care, coatings, food and nutrition, lubricants, synthesis, and plastics industries. ORIGINAL: Norwegian state owned electricity company Statkraft announced that it has agreed to acquire a 70.5% stake in Chilean peer Empresa Electrica Pilmaiquen for an undisclosed amount. The purchase of the majority stake will trigger a mandatory tender offer to all shareholders, which Pilmaiquen estimates to be launched at USD 4.87 per share. As of 25 February 2015, Pilmaiquen had 50,000,000 common shares outstanding. Based on the estimated tender offer price, the deal value (consideration) for the 70.5% stake acquired by Statkraft would equal USD 171.6mn. The sellers in the deal include MBI Corredores (4.4%), Inversiones y Asesorias GGF (9.2%), Inmobiliaria e Inversiones Le Roc (2.7%), Inversiones Andyara (8.3%), Sozhou Ltda (0.1%), Inversiones Antillanca, Inversiones Arlequín Dos, Inversiones Ruisenor Dos (10.82%) and Compania de Inversiones Rio Bueno (26.5%). Statkraft said that the acquisition strengthens its position in Chile and expands its project portfolio for further growth within international hydropower. Empresa Electrica Pilmaiquen owns and operates the 52.5 MW Rucatayo hydroelectric power plant in south Chile. The company also holds water rights for three hydro-power projects in the same river. Pilmaiquen is listed on the Santiago Stock Exchange and booked revenues of CLP 19.5bn (USD 35.1mn) in 2014. Statkraft is engaged in hydroelectric power, wind power and gas-fired power generation, and district heating. The company employs some 3,700 people in more than 20 countries. In 2014, Statkraft booked revenues of NOK 48.3bn (USD 8.21bn). ORIGINAL: U.K.-based packaging manufacturer DS Smith announced that it reached an agreement to acquire Austrian peer Duropack for an enterprise value of around EUR 300mn (USD 341.5mn). The seller is One Equity Partners, the private equity arm of US financial institution JPMorgan Chase & Co. It acted via its subsidiary CP Group 2 BV. Duropack operates in nine countries: Austria, Hungary, Bosnia, Bulgaria, Macedonia, Serbia, Slovakia, Croatia and Slovenia. One Equity Partners, established in 2001, has committed more than USD 11bn in private equity investments in 73 companies across various industries, including chemicals, healthcare, technology, travel and manufacturing. The shares will be acquired at a price of EGP 280.7 apiece, a 73% premium to the company's closing stock price of EGP 162.7 on 22 February 2015. Following the transaction, Orange will hold around a 99% stake in ECMS. The transaction is expected to complete in Q1 2015. ECMS, which operates under the brand name MobilNil, was founded in 1998. The company has 4299 sites, 36 switches and 25 mobile BTSs. It has 33 million customers. ECMS posted revenues of EGP 10.6bn (EUR 1.16bn) and net loss of EGP 456.7mn (EUR 50mn) in 2013. Orange is one of the world's leading telecommunications operators. The company is present in 30 countries in Europe, Asia and Africa, with a customer base of over 240 million people as of 30 September 2014. Its shares are listed on the NYSE Euronext Paris and on the New York Stock Exchange. It employs 159,000 people, and generated revenues of EUR 39.4bn and net income of EUR 925mn in 2014. OTMT is an investment holding company. ORIGINAL: German automotive components manufacturer MAHLE GmbH has agreed to acquire the thermal division of U.K.-headquartered global automotive supplier Delphi Automotive PLC for a cash consideration of USD 727mn (EUR 670mn), both parties announced on their websites. The transaction is subject to regulatory approval and is expected to close in the third quarter of 2015. The deal consideration values the thermal business at an implied last-twelve-month (LTM) EV/EBITDA multiple of 9.5x. The acquisition is in line with MAHLE's strategy to expand its thermal business. MAHLE also signed a separate agreement to acquire Delphi's stake in Delphi Automotive Air-Conditioning System Co Ltd located in Shanghai, China. ORIGINAL: Chilean hotel and casino operator Dream SA announced that it has entered into a Memorandum of Understanding with South African hotels & casinos management company Sun International Ltd pursuant to which the companies will merge their Latin American operations. Financial terms were not disclosed. Under the agreement, Dream will acquire and absorb the Latin American subsidiary of Sun International. As a result of this, the current shareholders of Dream will own 50% of the combined entity, while the shareholders of Sun International will own the remaining 50%. The agreement also stipulates that following completion of the merger, Sun International will increase its share in Dream up to 55% via a combination of acquiring USD 40mn in additional shares from Dream's current shareholders and of subscribing for USD 25mn newly issued shares of the company. The existing executive team of Dream will continue managing the combined entity, which will remain the sole vehicle through which the Chilean and the South African hotel and casino operators will develop their business in Latin America. The CEOs of both firms said that this operation will expand the companies' Latin American presence, providing a platform for future expansion. Dream concluded that the parties intend to list the company on the Santiago Stock Exchange via an IPO during the next two years, following completion of the merger. The transaction is subject to regulatory and other approvals and is expected to close during the third quarter of 2015. The operations of the Latin American subsidiary of Sun International include 100% ownership of the Ocean Sun casino in Panama, 100% in a casino project near completion in Colombia, and 44% in the Chilean casino Monticello. Back in July 2014, Sun International agreed to acquire a 54.7% stake in Monticello for USD 114mn, a transaction which is currently pending and when completed will boost the South African firm's interest in the casino to 98.9%. Dream's and Sun International's Latin American operations generated unaudited EBITDA of approximately USD 100mn for 2014. The merged entity will have 6,642 slots and 295 gaming tables distributed across 12 licenses in four countries. Dream is a Chilean hotel and casino operator. It is controlled 51% by Chilean entrepreneurs Claudio Fischer & Humberto Fischer and 49% by Citi Venture Capital International, a private equity firm of U.S. bank Citigroup which invests in emerging markets. The company operates six casinos in Chile: Iquique, Temuco, Valdivia, Puerto Varas, Coyhaique and Punta Arenas, and has also expanded into Peru. It posted sales revenues of almost CLP 87bn (USD 173mn) and net income of CLP 6.2bn (around USD 12mn) for 2013. Sun International operates in the entertainment and leisure business. ORIGINAL: Brazilian renewable energy company Statkraft Investimentos announced the acquisition of a 36.85% stake in Brazilian electricity generator Desenvix Energias Renovaveis SA from local holding company Jackson Empreendimentos Ltda. The deal is valued at BRL 500mn (USD 175mn), the Wall Street Journal reported. With the acquisition, Statkraft will own 81.3% of the target's capital. The transaction is subject to regulatory approval by the Brazilian antitrust competition regulator CADE and the Brazilian electricity sector watchdog Aneel, as well as by investment management fund Funcef, the third majority shareholder in Desenvix. The operation is expected to be completed during the second quarter of 2015. Jackson Empreendimentos is an investment vehicle of Engevix Group. After the conclusion of the deal, Desenvix's assets will be composed of six hydroelectric plants, minority interests in four hydroelectric plants, an eolic park in Bahia's state encompassing three plants, minority interests in two transmission assets and a portfolio of several projects in hydroelectric energy. Desenvix, headquartered in Barueri (Sao Paulo state) and established in 1995, is a producer of electricity from various renewable sources, such as hydroelectric power, thermoelectric power, wind farms, and biomass fired power plants. Desenvix was formerly known as Desenvix SA and in 2010 changed its name to Desenvix Energias Renovaveis SA. The company develops projects for power generation, electricity distribution and telecommunications support. Desenvix is controlled by Jackson Empreendimentos Ltda, by SN Power Energy of Brazil Ltda and FUNCEF, each holding respectively 40.65%, 40.65% and 18.70% of the company's capital. Desenvix Energias Renovaveis SA's debentures are listed on the BM&FBOVESPA Stock Exchange and the company posted revenues of BRL 185.4mn (USD 86.08mn) and a net loss of BRL 31.7mn (USD 14.7mn) in 2013. Statkraft Investimentos is part of Norwegian state owned electricity company Statkraft, a leading international producer of hydroelectric power and Europe's largest generator of renewable energy. Statkraft produces hydropower, wind power, gas-fired power and district heating, and is a global player in energy market operations. Statkraft employs about 3,700 employees in more than 20 countries. Statkraft posted revenues of NOK 48.2bn (USD 7.69bn) and a net profit of NOK 3.9bn (USD 619.9mn) in 2014. Jackson Empreendimentos SA, founded in 1998 and based in Barueri in the state of Sao Paulo, is a holding company of the Engevix Group. Engevix is a Brazilian company founded in 1965, that provides a wide range of services from feasibility studies, consulting engineering and project management to fully-integrated solutions. The company operates both in the public and private sectors in Brazil and abroad, and engages in the energy (generation, transmission and distribution), oil, gas, petrochemical, basic industries (pulp and paper, steel, mining, etc.) and infrastructure areas. _____________________________________________________________________________ UPDATE 3: Em 13 de Julho de 2015, a Desenvix anunciou a conclusão da operação. According to Mr. Bob Eck, President and CEO of Anixter, the transaction allows Anixter International to focus on its core Enterprise Cabling and Security Solutions, and Electrical and Electronic Wire and Cable segments. In addition, it provides the buyer with funds to make investments and strategic acquisitions. Mr. Eck added that the operation provides Fasteners business with an operational expertise and financial resources to drive its growth in the industry. Mr. Eric Baroyan, Partner at AIP, said that Fasteners business is a leading global original equipment manufacturer (OEM) supplier with a great potential for future growth. The Anixter's Fasteners business manufactures and distributes fasteners for customers in the heavy truck, power train, luxury automotive, and other segments. It operates 73 distribution centers, 12 quality labs and has more than 1,900 employees around the world. The business had a turnover of USD 938.5mn and an operating profit of USD 39.1mn in fiscal year ended 2 January 2014. AIP is a middle-market private equity firm, focused on North American-based industrial businesses with global operations. As of 12 February 2015, AIP had completed more than 50 transactions and had USD 1.1bn in equity capital. AIP invests in corporate divestitures, management buyouts, recapitalisations, and other businesses, with revenues between USD 100mn and USD 750mn. Anixter is a global distributor of enterprise cabling and security solutions, electrical and electronic wire and cable, and OEM supply fasteners. The company provides innovative inventory management programs, offers 500,000 products, operates approximately 270 warehouses, as well as 300 locations in 50 countries. Abengoa Yield is a dividend growth-oriented company established in December 2013 by Abengoa in order to own a portfolio of renewable energy, conventional power and electric transmission assets located primarily in North and South America, and previously owned by Abengoa and its subsidiaries. The assets included the two solar energy projects Solana (280 MW) and Mojave (280 MW) located in the United States, a 300 MW gas-fired cogeneration facility called ACT located in Mexico, the three electric transmission lines Quadra 1, Quadra 2 and Palmucho with combined length of 140km in Chile, the two electric transmission lines ATN and ATS with combined length of 1498km in Peru, the 50 MW wind energy project Palmatir located in Uruguay, and the two solar energy projects Solaben 2 (50 MW) and Solaben 3 (50 MW) located in Spain. All the assets are wholly-owned by Abengoa, except for the Solaben 2 and 3 projects, which are 70%-owned by Abengoa, with the remaining 30% being held by Japanese trading company Itochu Corp. Abengoa Yield raised USD 828mn in an IPO on the NASDAQ Stock Market back in June 2014 in exchange for 34.13% of its enlarged capital. The company added that it will distribute almost all the proceeds to Abengoa, as part of the consideration payable to Abengoa for transferring the above-mentioned assets following its establishment. Prior to the IPO, Abengoa Yield was a wholly-owned subsidiary of Abengoa. As of 30 September 2014, Abengoa had 64.28% interest in Abengoa Yield. Abengoa provides technology solutions for sustainable development in the energy and environment sectors. The company operates in three segments: engineering and construction, concession-type infrastructure and industrial production. It is engaged in the generation of electricity from renewable sources, in the manufacturing of biofuels, in the construction of infrastructures in the energy sector, as well as in the desalination of seawater and recycling of industrial waste. Com a operação a LG se tornará a única empresa no Brasil exclusivamente focada em recursos humanos incorporada com ferramentas HCMS, que incluem funções de recursos humanos estratégicas, com ferramentas de gestão de empregados, remuneração e recompensas, recrutamento e contratação, gestão de talentos e ferramentas de aprendizagem. Os co-fundadores da W3net, Ricardo e Cibele Vasconcelos, atuarão como diretores tecnológicos e comerciais. De acordo com o jornal local Valor Internacional, com a aquisição, a H.I.G. investiu no Brasil mais de BRL 2.7bn (USD 1bn) de sua carteira de investimento global de BRL 46.1bn (USD 17bn). A mesma fonte afirma ainda que o comprador é conhecido por seus investimentos em pequenas e médias empresas com EBITDA que variem entre BRL 15mn (USD 5.5mn) e BRL 70mn (USD 25.8mn). A W3net, com sede em Belo Horizonte, no estado brasileiro de Minas Gerais, é um líder de mercado no fornecimento de software de gerenciamento de desempenho e desenvolvimento profissional, através dos Sistemas de SaaS Gestão de Capital Humano (SaaS HCMS). A empresa lida com mais de 90 clientes em diferentes indústrias e emprega cerca de 200 funcionários. A LG lugar de gente, fundada em 1985 e localizada no estado brasileiro de Goiás, é um fornecedor de software de gestão de recursos humanos, com uma carteira de mais de 400 empresas de diferentes setores no Brasil. A empresa normalmente oferece soluções para empresas com mais de 5,000 funcionários. A LG também tem escritórios em Minas Gerais, Paraná, Pernambuco, Rio de Janeiro e de São Paulo. A H.I.G. Capital LLC, criada em 1993 e com sede em Miami, EUA, é uma empresa global de investimentos em 'private equity', capital de risco e ativos alternativos especializada no fornecimento de dívida e capital próprio para pequenas e médias empresas. Desde a sua criação, a empresa tem gerido e investido em mais de 200 empresas em todo o mundo. A H.I.G. ORIGINAL: Japanese multinational trading company Sumitomo Corporation has announced an agreement to acquire a 65% stake in Brazilian distributor of farm and livestock supplies Agro Amazonia Produtos Agropecuarios Ltda, for an undisclosed amount. The acquisition represents the first investment by a Japanese multinational in the distribution and supply of inputs in the state of Mato Grosso, where the target operates. Agro Amazonia expects that with Sumitomo's resources (financing, logistics, marketing, etc.) it will be able to increase its sales to more than USD 500mn by 2019, which represents more than double of current sales levels. According to the official press release, the fact that Brazil is the second largest world market producer of soybeans and the third largest in corn production, contributed to Sumitomo's decision to enter the Brazilian agricultural sector. Mato Grosso, located in the mid-west part of the country, is two and a half times as large as Japan and exhibits an appropriate climate for grain and seed production. Based on this propensity and the growth of the soybean and corn planting areas over the last decade, the region is projected to have a 5% to 8% market expansion in the agricultural materials, agrochemical, seeds and fertilizers' sector. The state is also the largest producer of granary, soybean, cotton, maize, sunflower and beef cattle in Brazil. Agro Amazonia Produtos Agropecuarios Ltda, founded in 1983, is one of the largest agribusiness sector-based companies in the State of Mato Grosso. A aquisição representa o primeiro investimento de uma multinacional japonesa na distribuição e fornecimento de agropecuários no estado do Mato Grosso, onde a empresa-alvo detém a maior parte dos seus negócios. A Agro Amazônia espera que com os recursos da Sumitomo (financiamento, logística, marketing , etc), será capaz de alcançar um aumento nas vendas até aos USD 500mn em 2019, o que representa mais que o dobro dos níveis de vendas atuais. De acordo com o comunicado de imprensa oficial, o fato de que o Brasil é o segundo maior produtor de soja mundial e o terceiro maior na produção de milho, contribuíram para a decisão da Sumitomo de entrar no setor agrícola brasileiro. Mato Grosso, localizado na parte centro-oeste do país, é duas vezes e meia maior que o Japão e apresenta um clima apropriado para a produção de grãos e de sementes. Com base nesta tendência e no crescimento das áreas de plantação de soja e milho ao longo da última década, a região é projetada para ter uma expansão de 5 a 8% nos mercados dos setores agrícola, agroquímico, de sementes e fertilizantes. O estado também é o maior produtor de celeiro, soja, algodão, milho, girassol e gado bovino no Brasil. ORIGINAL: Ireland-based building company CRH announced that it has signed an agreement to acquire certain assets of Swiss cement maker Holcim and of French building materials producer Lafarge for an enterprise value of EUR 6.5bn (USD 7.33bn). The transaction will be funded by EUR 2bn cash from balance sheet, new debt and a 9.99% equity placing. The deal is a part of planned merger between Holcim and Lafarge. The acquired assets will be separated in a company provisionally referred to as NewCo. NewCo is engaged in the production of cement, aggregates, ready-mix and related construction activities. It operates in Canada, U.S., UK, Romania, Serbia, Slovakia, Hungary, Germany, France, Brazil and the Philippines. NewCo has 24 integrated cement plants together with 10 grinding stations for a total capacity of approximately 36 million tonnes per annum. It employs 15,000 people. In 2013, the company produced 23mt of cement, 79mt of aggregates, 8mt of Asphalt and 10m m3 of RMC. NewCo expects revenues of EUR 5.1bn and EBITDA of EUR 752mn in 2014. CRH was established in 1970. The company manufactures cement, aggregates, concrete products and asphalt. It employs some 76,000 people at 3,500 operating locations in 35 countries. CRH is listed on the Dublin, London and New York stock exchanges. It had revenues of EUR 18bn and a net loss of EUR 296mn in 2013. Holcim, established in 1912, specialises in manufacturing and distribution of cement, ready-mix concrete, asphalt and aggregates (crushed stone, sand and gravel). The company operates 617 cement and aggregates plants with annual production capacity of 217.5 million tons of cement in 70 countries across all continents, and engages 73,000 employees. Holcim is listed on the Six Swiss Exchange and the London Stock Exchange. It reached a turnover of CHF 19.7bn (EUR 16.1bn) and a net income of CHF 1.27bn (EUR 1.04bn) in 2013. Lafarge produces and supplies a wide range of building materials, mainly cement, aggregates, concrete and gypsum products. The company employs 65,000 people, and posted revenues of EUR 15.2bn and a net profit of EUR 601mn in 2013. Note 1: The Deal Value is assumed to be equal to the disclosed Enterprise Value. Financial details on the deal were not disclosed, but according to 99Taxis president Paulo Veras the amount was well more than BRL 5mn (USD 1.86mn) usually received by companies obtaining series A financing. Previous investors in 99Taxis, venture capital firms Monashees Capital and Qualcomm Ventures also took part in the latest financing. 99Taxis said it plans to increase the number of its employees from 100 to 150. 99 Taxis Desenvolvimento de Softwares Ltda was founded in 2012 and has developed an application that allows users to request taxis by phone. The company operates in over 399 cities and more than 100,000 taxis use its app. Tiger Global, established in 2001 by US private investors Julian Robertson and Charles Coleman, is a global investment firm specialised in private equity and public equity investments in the technology, telecom, media, retail and consumer sectors. The company is based in New York with additional offices in Beijing and Singapore. Monashees Capital, established in 2005, is a venture capital firm, focused on investments in the internet and educational sectors. The company usually invests between BRL 0.5mn (USD 0.19mn) and BRL 5mn (USD 1.86mn). Its portfolio comprises Brazilian IT firms Algentis, Peixe Urbano, boo-box, Elo7, Mind Lab, VivaReal and Baby.com.br. Qualcomm Ventures, founded in 2000 as the venture capital investment arm of U.S. mobility solutions provider Qualcomm Inc, focuses on investments in companies from the mobile software, consumer internet, healthcare, energy, e-commerce and digital media segments. The company usually invests between USD 0.5mn and USD 10mn in a single transaction. _____________________________________________________________________________________ A 99 Taxis Desenvolvimento de Softwares Ltda (99Taxis), desenvolvedor brasileiro de aplicativos móveis para táxis, conseguiu financiamento da empresa de gestão de investimentos norte-americana Tiger Global Management, relatou o techcrunch.com. The value of the deal is estimated at EUR 285.7mn. The transaction is part of a global deal that includes assets of Holcim and Lafarge in Brazil, Hungary, the Philippines, Romania, Serbia, Canada, France, Germany, the U.K. and the U.S., and has a total enterprise value of EUR 6.5bn (USD 7.33bn). The deal is a part of planned merger between Holcim and Lafarge, in which both companies have to dispose of certain assets in order to gain regulatory approval. The acquired assets will be separated in a company provisionally referred to as NewCo. NewCo is engaged in the production of cement, aggregates, ready-mix and related construction activities. It operates in Canada, U.S., UK, Romania, Serbia, Slovakia, Hungary, Germany, France, Brazil and the Philippines. NewCo has 24 integrated cement plants together with 10 grinding stations for a total capacity of approximately 36 million tonnes per annum. It employs 15,000 people. In 2013, the company produced 23mt of cement, 79mt of aggregates, 8mt of Asphalt and 10m m3 of RMC. NewCo expects revenues of EUR 5.1bn (USD 6.77bn) and EBITDA of EUR 752mn (USD 999mn) in 2014. Holcim operates in Slovakia through the company Holcim (Slovensko) as. It employs 932 people and has annual production capacity of 3.5 million tones of cement. CRH, established in 1970, manufactures cement, aggregates, concrete products and asphalt. It employs some 90,000 people at 4,000 operating locations in 37 countries. CRH is listed on the Dublin, London and New York stock exchanges. It had revenues of EUR 18.9bn (USD 25.1bn) and a net income of EUR 582mn (USD 773.5mn) in 2014. Holcim, established in 1912, specialises in manufacturing and distribution of cement, ready-mix concrete, asphalt and aggregates (crushed stone, sand and gravel). The company operates 617 cement and aggregates plants with annual production capacity of 217.5 million tons of cement in 70 countries across all continents, and engages 73,000 employees. Holcim is listed on the Six Swiss Exchange and the London Stock Exchange. It reached a turnover of CHF 19.1bn (EUR 21bn) in 2014. Lafarge produces and supplies a wide range of building materials, mainly cement, aggregates, concrete and gypsum products. The company employs 65,000 people, and posted revenues of EUR 12.84bn (USD 17bn) and a net profit of EUR 143mn (USD 190mn) in 2014. ORIGINAL: U.S.-based chemical and technology products firm The Lubrizol Corporation, has announced the acquisition of Brazilian peer EcoQuimica Industria e Comercio Produtos Quimicos Ltda for an undisclosed sum. The Vice-president and General Manager of subsidiary Lubrizol Performance Coatings Tesh Gor, said that "the acquisition will enable Lubrizol to broaden our already comprehensive portfolio on a global basis and provide us a stronger local presence in this [Brazilian] market", thus expanding Lubrizol's performance coatings reach in Latin America. The transaction includes all of EcoQuimica's intellectual property, trademarks and customer lists. Furthermore, Lubrizol also purchased a piece of real estate next to EcoQuimica's facility in order to support upcoming expansions. EcoQuimica Industria e Comercio Produtos Quimicos Ltda, based in the municipality of Paulinia in the state of Sao Paulo, was founded in 1999 and is a manufacturer and supplier of coatings technology for decorative paints, textiles, cement, elastomeric and paper coatings products. EcoQuimica was formerly under common ownership with Mercia Industria e Comercio Produtos Quimica Ltda.. The Lubrizol Corporation, a Berkshire Hathaway company established in 1928 and located in Wickliffe, in the U.S. State of Ohio, is a global producer and supplier of chemicals technology in the transportation, industrial and consumer markets. Its products include lubricant additives for engine oils, other transportation-related fluids and industrial lubricants, along with additives for gasoline and diesel fuel. Also, Lubrizol is involved in manufacturing ingredients and additives for home care and personal products and pharmaceuticals, which include plastics technology as well as performance coatings in the form of specialty resins and additives. Lubrizol has manufacturing facilities in 17 countries and many other offices around the world. It employs nearly 7,000 people worldwide. ________________________________________________________________________________________ UPDATE: Em 3 de junho de 2015, o assessor jurídico do comprador anunciou que o negócio foi concluído em 29 de dezembro de 2014. The transaction was carried out through the acquisition of local investment management company EKOPUR d.o.o, which holds the 7.1% stake in Geoplin. Following the acquisition, Petrol will increase its stake in Geoplin to 39.1%. Other large shareholders in Geoplin are the Slovenian government with 39.6% and local financial investment company Salnal with 7.5%. The transaction is in line with E.ON's strategy to focus on its domestic market and to exit the CEE region. Geoplin was founded in 1974 and engages in the supply, trade, representation and intermediation of natural gas in Slovenia and internationally. The company's customer base includes large industrial consumers, distributors and users directly connected to the natural gas transmission network. In 2013, it registered sales revenue of EUR 321mn and a net profit of EUR 8.24mn. Petrol was incorporated in 1947 and it supplies oil and other energy products to Slovenia, BiH, Croatia, Serbia, Montenegro and Kosovo. The company trades petroleum products, including heating oil, bottled gas and petroleum, as well as energy products: electricity, natural gas, liquefied petroleum gas and district heating. Hidrovias do Brasil, founded in 2010 by P2 Brasil, a joint-venture between local asset manager Patria Investimentos and Brazilian engineering firm Grupo Promon, is a pre-operational company, specialised in the development and operation of inland and sea terminals integrated with barging operations, and the provision of integrated logistic services on five waterway corridors: North, Southeast, South, Parana-Paraguay and Colombia. Hidrovias do Brasil posted BRL 3.09mn (USD 1.43mn) in revenues and a net loss of BRL 8mn (USD 3.71mn) in 2013. IFC, a unit of the World Bank, is a global institution promoting sustainable economic growth in developing countries by providing capital and advisory/risk services to business and governments. The company has private enterprises in more than 100 countries worldwide. BNDESPar, established in 1982 as the investment arm of federal development bank Banco Nacional de Desenvolvimento Economico e Social (BNDES), focuses on direct investments through private equity, venture capital, and debentures in growth companies, operating in the information technology and communications, renewable energy, oil and gas, biotechnology and life sciences, green chemistry, second-generation ethanol, infrastructure, and transportation sectors. _________________________________________________________________________________ UPDATE: Em 20 de março de 2015, a Hidrovias do Brasil anunciou a conslusão do acordo. ORIGINAL: Brazilian equipment and services supplier to the oil and gas sector Lupatech SA announced that it has agreed to sell its Argentine industrial automation equipment subsidiary Jefferson Sudamericana to Argentine private investors Ricardo and Felipe Menendez for USD 5.7mn. The deal includes Jefferson Sudamericana's related entities Jefferson Solenoid Valves USA, Valjeff. and Jefferson Solenoidbras and the buyers will carry out the purchase through Uruguay-based firms Jikur and Jatdery. The deal is part of Lupatech's pre-packaged reorganisation plan, announced in November 2013, aiming to restructure its capital structure and lower its indebtedness. The plan involved debt reprofiling in addition to swapping 85% of company's perpetual and convertible bonds (est. USD 460mn) for new equity. In June 2014, the reorganisation plan was approved by the competent Brazilian and U.S. Bankruptcy Courts. Jefferson Sudamericana manufactures solenoid valves, magnetic level switches and other industrial automation equipment. The company has a portfolio of over 3,000 products and serves clients from the petroleum, engineering, construction, food and beverage, heating, automobile, metallurgical, textile, and chemical and petrochemical industries among other. Lupatech, established in 1980, is one of the largest equipment and services suppliers to the oil and gas sector in Brazil, with operations in two business segments: Products (anchoring ropes for production platforms, valves, completion tools and gas compressors) and Services (workover, drilling, well intervention, coating and pipe inspection services). The company operates 31 units in Brazil, Colombia and Argentina, and has some 2,900 employees. ORIGINAL: Austrian do-it-yourself chain bauMax has decided to exit the Hungarian market transferring its local stores to Austrian furniture retailer XXXLutz for an undisclosed amount, XXXLutz announced in a press release published on its website. The 13 Hungarian bauMax stores are expected to be transferred under XXXLutz's ownership by April 2015. The transaction will be carried out by XXXLutz through its Hungarian subsidiary Möbelix Kft. The new owner will convert the 13 units with a cumulated surface area of 350,000m2 in Möbelix furniture stores, expending the existing network to 16 stores. XXXLutz is planning further expansions on the Hungarian market, one Möbelix store is due to open at the end of February 2014. Also the group intends to open two XXXLutz branded stores and eight MömaX stores. bauMax AG has announced its intention to exit the Hungarian market due to the unfavourable market conditions, the Hungarian DIY market has been in recession since 2007. The Austrian player announced it plans to concentrate its activities in Austria, the Czech Republic and Slovakia. bauMax was established in Hungary in 1992. It employs around 800 people and for 2014 it registered revenues of HUF 23.1bn (USD 83.05mn) and losses of HUF 3.2bn (USD 11.5mn). Its parent company bauMax AG was founded in 1976 and is currently operating in five countries: the Czech Republic, Croatia, Slovakia, Slovenia and Austria. ORIGINAL Indian wind turbine manufacturer Suzlon Energy Ltd has agreed to sell its German unit Senvion SE to U.S.-based private equity firm Centerbridge Partners LP for a total cash consideration of EUR 1bn (USD 1.1bn), the seller announced. The deal is subject to regulatory approvals and customary closing conditions. Under the agreement, Suzlon could receive a future earn-out of up to EUR 50mn (USD 57.9mn), depending on the target's performance. Suzlon will give Senvion the license for offshore technology for the Indian market while Suzlon will give license to Senvion for the S111-2.1 MW technology for the U.S. market. In October 2012, the seller defaulted on its U.S. dollar-denominated convertible bonds worth USD 209mn. As a result, the company entered a debt restructuring plan that includes a two-year moratorium on principal and interest payments, a decrease of interest rate, an eight-year extension of payment after the moratorium and equity placement to lenders. Suzlon will use the proceeds from the sale to reduce its debt and focus on high growth markets such as India and the U.S.A., as well as other emerging markets. Senvion SE manufactures, develops and markets onshore and offshore wind turbines. It also provides turnkey, service and maintenance, transport, and installation, in addition to foundation planning and construction services. The company posted revenues of EUR 1.8bn (USD 2.5bn) in 2014. Centerbridge Partners LP acts as a private investment firm focused on private equity, credit investments, leverage buyouts and distressed securities. The company manages over USD 20bn of assets and has offices in New York and London. Suzlon Energy Ltd is one of the largest wind turbine manufacturers globally in terms of annual installed capacity and market share. It has operations in 31 countries and has wind energy capacity of over 25 million kW. The company's revenues were IND 202.1bn (USD 3.4bn) for FY ended 31 March 2014.
